scp -r acptransfer/ tomgdow@172.28.128.3:/home/tomgdow

# Worked perfectly.

tomgdow@172.28.128.3 is address of 'remote' machine, 
where address obtained by running hostname -I on that machine

See here for a good ref to scp

http://www.hypexr.org/linux_scp_help.php
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11304895/how-to-scp-a-folder-from-remote-to-local


